query.result:
46 Because there is no rain, no hail, no snow, 47 no dew, no frost any more falls down 48 than the short ladder of three steps;
49 thick clouds do not appear nor thin, 50 nor coruscate, nor daughter of Taumante, 51 which from there often changes districts;
52 dry vapor does not rise any more forward 53 than to the top of the three steps that I spoke, 54 where the vicar of Peter has the plants.

55 It trembles perhaps more down little or much;  
56 but for wind that in earth hides itself,  
57 I do not know how, here up never trembled.

