109 Io pur sorrisi come l’uom ch’ammicca; 110 per che l’ombra si tacque, e riguardommi 111 ne li occhi ove ’l sembiante più si ficca;
112 e «Se tanto labore in bene assommi», 113 disse, «perché la tua faccia testeso 114 un lampeggiar di riso dimostrommi?».

query.result:
109 I indeed smiled like the man who winks;  
110 so that the shadow fell silent, and looked back at me  
111 in the eyes where the likeness sticks the most;  

112 and “If you sum up so much labor into good”,  
113 he said, “why your face itself  
114 a flash of laughter shows me?”.

121 Wherefore I: “Perhaps that you marvel,  
122 ancient spirit, of the laughter that I made;  
123 but more of amazement I want that you take.”
